info = "[gd]LocationLOD[/gd] class provides functionality to \"bake\" a LOD model with one diffuse material to save draw-calls amount.

[c]Usage example[/c]
[gd]
LocationLOD.bake_LOD_mesh(sample_mesh_LOD, self.mesh.resource_path)
yield(LocationLOD, \"bake_complete\")
# Store results
var data = LocationLOD.get_baked_LOD_data()
var mesh_LOD = data.mesh
# ...
[/gd]

That's really what you need to know about this thing. If you want to see usage of it in current implementations, check [gd]LocationProp[/gd], [gd]LocationBlockoutMesh[/gd] and [gd]LocationMeshCombiner[/gd].

